Given the following array of integers:

A = [64, 25, 12, 22, 11]

Apply the Selection Sort algorithm to sort the array in ascending order.
Show the array after each pass of the algorithm.
Write the Selection Sort algorithm (pseudocode).
State the time complexity of Selection Sort in best, average, and worst cases.
class Main {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        int[] arr = {1, 4, 2, 5, 7};

        for (int i = 0; i < arr.length - 1; i++) {
            int min = i;

            for (int j = i + 1; j < arr.length; j++) {
                if (arr[j] < arr[min]) {
                    min = j;
                }
            }

            // Swap
            int temp = arr[min];
            arr[min] = arr[i];
            arr[i] = temp;
        }

        // Print sorted array
        for (int i = 0; i < arr.length; i++) {
            System.out.print(arr[i] + " ");
        }
    }
}
